meanings.definition: Not having a label or tag attached.
meanings.sent1: The unlabeled box sat in the corner of the room.
meanings.sent2: She bought an unlabeled dress at the thrift store.
meanings.sent3: The unlabeled jar in the fridge turned out to be pickles, not jam.
meanings.sent4: His unlabeled emotions were a mystery to everyone around him.
meanings.sent5: The unlabeled map confused the hikers and led them astray.

meanings.sent1: The unlabeled package arrived at the doorstep.
meanings.sent2: The museum displayed an unlabeled painting of unknown origin.
meanings.sent3: The unlabeled student caused confusion in the classroom.
meanings.sent4: Her thoughts were like unlabeled boxes, waiting to be unpacked.
meanings.sent5: The unlabeled ingredients in the recipe added an element of surprise to the dish.
